        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 22 at 2:04AM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 204 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 20
miles west of Baker, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch size hail, along with
heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Baker, Plevna, Ismay, Westmore, Willard and Ollie.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
